# Frontend rules (Senju)

Follow **`docs/frontend/README.md`** and the ADRs it references on every change.

## Non-negotiables

- **Stack:** Next.js (App Router) + React + **TypeScript strict mode**. No implicit `any`. No `any` without an inline justification comment.
- **Package manager:** pnpm. Use the committed lockfile.
- **Styling:** Tailwind utilities only, consuming design tokens. No raw hex values in component code. No inline `style` for design-system values.
- **Components:** shadcn/ui primitives live in our repo under `frontend/src/components/ui/`; Radix powers behavior. Follow the three-tier layout from `docs/frontend/design-system.md` §9.
- **Server/client boundary:** Default to server components. Add `"use client"` only when hooks, browser APIs, event handlers, or client-only libs require it. Never import `server-only` code from a client component.
- **Data contracts:** Consume the backend via the OpenAPI-generated TS client from `backend/openapi/openapi.yaml`. Do not hand-type request/response shapes.
- **Forms:** React Hook Form + Zod. Validation schemas mirror the OpenAPI contract.

## Testing (merge gates)

- Unit + interaction tests with Vitest + React Testing Library for every component and non-trivial hook.
- **jest-axe** a11y assertion for every interactive component.
- **Storybook** stories for every component — default, variants × sizes, loading/empty/error, disabled, long content.
- **Playwright** route-level E2E for every shipped route.
- Coverage is not a target; meaningful branch coverage is.

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA is a floor)

- Keyboard reachable + visible focus on every interactive element.
- `aria-label` on icon-only buttons — lint-enforced.
- Color is never the only signal.
- `prefers-reduced-motion` respected on every animation.
- See `docs/frontend/accessibility.md`.

## Performance budgets

- Marketing route: ≤ 150 KB JS (gzip), LCP ≤ 2.0s.
- Authenticated console: ≤ 250 KB JS (gzip) first load, TTI ≤ 3.0s.
- Virtualize lists > 100 rows.
- Tree-shake icons (import per icon from `lucide-react`).

## PR expectations (in addition to `senju-workflow`)

- Link to one issue, complete the PR template.
- Include **keyboard-only walkthrough** in test evidence for any interactive change.
- Storybook stories updated for any component change.
- Attach a screenshot of the final UI in both themes for any visual change.
- If tokens change, `pnpm test:contrast` output included in test evidence.

When unsure, cite `docs/frontend/` and the ADRs in review.
